Looters have burned shacks in Marabastad, Grant Street. Courtesy of #DSTV403 PRETORIA - Police are monitoring Marabastad after shacks were set alight on Monday afternoon. This as widespread attacks on foreign nationals and looting of their shops continue. READ: Xenophobia not behind Pretoria chaos: authorities Shacks were set alight in Grant Street where many foreign nationals live. An eyewitness said a woman started the fire. "We have our belongings here, everything is burnt down," she said. READ: Violence raging across Gauteng CBDs No injuries have been reported. Residents have said they don't know where they will sleep.